{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:49+0000", "md5": "C0BE1EC6670845A812B975554AFBE5CA", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "OE", "normalizedForm": "OE", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 2}, "context": "OE provides support for Intel SGX as well as preview support for ARM TrustZone, thus aiming to generalize the development of enclave applications across TEEs. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001043081283569336}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.1069643497467041}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.3113021850585938e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.26348876953125}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.1069643497467041}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.3113021850585938e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "The code of the Core and Data Tasks are written using Open Enclave (OE) [7], an SDK for developing enclave applications in C/C++. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005263686180114746}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 17}, "context": "Besides, the code of each Data Task is sandboxed [10] within its enclave to preclude any voluntary data leakage outside the enclave by a malicious Data Task.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.23052442073822021}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00012731552124023438}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Ubuntu Linux", "normalizedForm": "Ubuntu Linux", "offsetStart": 17, "offsetEnd": 29}, "version": {"rawForm": "18.04", "normalizedForm": "18.04", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 35}, "context": "The machine runs Ubuntu Linux 18.04 with SGX DCAP 1.41. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8678619861602783}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.5497207641601562e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8678619861602783}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.5497207641601562e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 23}, "context": "In particular, the code extensions required to support advanced -specific-data-oriented computations cannot be part of a trusted code base for the PDMS.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00018829107284545898}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00036275386810302734}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0728836059570312e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 41, "offsetEnd": 45}, "context": "Data Tasks can run arbitrary application code, not necessarily trusted by the PDMS owner, thereby enabling extensiveness (like UDFs in traditional DBMSs).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.031990051269531e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00013244152069091797}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SQLite", "normalizedForm": "SQLite", "offsetStart": 44, "offsetEnd": 50}, "version": {"rawForm": "3", "normalizedForm": "3", "offsetStart": 53, "offsetEnd": 54}, "context": "The Core data management module is based on SQLite (v3). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9055169820785522}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.230571746826172e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9055169820785522}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.230571746826172e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 48, "offsetEnd": 52}, "context": "Data Tasks are introduced as a means to support code extensions, needed to deal with applicationspecific personal data management.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 53, "offsetEnd": 57}, "context": "However, the complexity of these applications (large code base, extensible and not proven) and their execution environment (e.g., web browser) make them vulnerable.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.35385513305664e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008399486541748047}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.0067901611328125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Open Enclave (OE)", "normalizedForm": "Open Enclave (OE)", "offsetStart": 54, "offsetEnd": 74}, "context": "The code of the Core and Data Tasks are written using Open Enclave (OE) [7], an SDK for developing enclave applications in C/C++. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005263686180114746}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005263686180114746}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "OE", "normalizedForm": "OE", "offsetStart": 69, "offsetEnd": 71}, "context": "The Core communication module uses the mbed TLS plugin integrated in OE to establish secure channels with the Data Task enclaves, remote parties or Apps.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.26348876953125}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001323223114013672}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.26348876953125}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.1069643497467041}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.3113021850585938e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 77, "offsetEnd": 81}, "context": "An enclave provides three properties: (i) isolation ensures that the enclave code cannot be influenced by an attacker; (ii) confidentiality ensures that the enclave data is hidden from any other process by encrypting the RAM; (iii) with attestation, the enclave can prove that its results were indeed produced by its genuine code.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00047528743743896484}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 8.83340835571289e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 79, "offsetEnd": 83}, "context": "The Core and each Data Task run in individual enclaves protecting the data and code execution confidentiality from the untrusted execution environment [6].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.19324523210525513}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001672506332397461}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 94, "offsetEnd": 98}, "context": "However, to guarantee the global security of the architecture combining trusted and untrusted code, all the untrusted code must be totally separated from the trusted computing base.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005602240562438965}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002599358558654785}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 96, "offsetEnd": 100}, "context": "Finally, (iii) extensiveness is required, meaning that arbitrary -application specific-function code must be supported to collect data (e.g., scrapper) and compute the results (e.g., computation goes beyond simple SQL and requires an extension of the PDMS).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.005227863788604736}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.045269012451172e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 111, "offsetEnd": 115}, "context": "Other TEE-based DBMS architectures, like stealthDB [8], favor extensibility by running large parts of the DBMS code outside enclaves, but this implies an honest-but-curious attacker model, considered unrealistic for user-side solutions.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.9458274841308594e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.506111145019531e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 118, "offsetEnd": 122}, "context": "However, to guarantee the global security of the architecture combining trusted and untrusted code, all the untrusted code must be totally separated from the trusted computing base.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005602240562438965}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002599358558654785}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 123, "offsetEnd": 127}, "context": "A final security element is thus to impose deterministic Data Tasks, i.e., producing the same result for the same function code run on the same input.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0009358525276184082}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0018270015716552734}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 129, "offsetEnd": 133}, "context": "In particular, the code extensions required to support advanced -specific-data-oriented computations cannot be part of a trusted code base for the PDMS.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00018829107284545898}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00036275386810302734}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.0728836059570312e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 155, "offsetEnd": 159}, "context": "Finally, sandboxing techniques within enclaves (e.g., Ryoan [10], SGXJail [17]) protect the leakage of confidential data manipulated by untrusted enclaved code by restricting its address space.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.139278411865234e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.198883056640625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 169, "offsetEnd": 173}, "context": "Virtual random APIs are provided to preserve legitimate uses, e.g., the need for sampling, and are \"reproducible\", e.g., random numbers use a seed based on the function code and input set.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002529025077819824}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00018519163131713867}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 193, "offsetEnd": 197}, "context": "Designing an extensive and secure PDMS architecture preserving usage with the guarantees defined above is a significant challenge, given the fundamental tension between security (small trusted code base) and extensiveness (rich data-driven tasks).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.614757537841797e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.24115979671478271}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 275, "offsetEnd": 279}, "context": "Then, we consider two attacks conducted by PDMS queriers -who are employers in the Green bonus scenario-, wishing to gain access to raw personal data of the PDMS user, using a legitimate granted execute privilege on manifests leveraging potentially corrupted Data Tasks -the code being potentially produced by the querier-.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.04196369647979736}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004239678382873535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 325, "offsetEnd": 329}, "context": "An enclave provides three properties: (i) isolation ensures that the enclave code cannot be influenced by an attacker; (ii) confidentiality ensures that the enclave data is hidden from any other process by encrypting the RAM; (iii) with attestation, the enclave can prove that its results were indeed produced by its genuine code.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00047528743743896484}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 8.83340835571289e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Google Maps", "normalizedForm": "Google Maps", "offsetStart": 387, "offsetEnd": 398}, "context": "To exemplify this trend, we consider the Green bonus scenario described below: 'Green bonus' scenario: Companies want to reward their employees having an ecological conduct, and thus monthly compute a green bonus (financial incentive) based on the number of commutes by bike. Figure 1 proposes a possible, user centered, workflow: GPS traces are collected from a reliable service (e.g., Google Maps), then processed locally (e.g., by the user's PDMS) and the result is delivered to the employer with a proof of compliance. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.006850183010101318}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00029844045639038086}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.291534423828125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.006850183010101318}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00029844045639038086}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.291534423828125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 485, "offsetEnd": 489}, "context": "One specificity in this scenario is to call for mutual security between stakeholders (employees, i.e., PDMS users, and employers, i.e., PDMS queriers): (i) privacy is needed to ensure employees that their detailed location history is not disclosed to third parties (including the employer); and (ii) verifiability must ensure employers that the computed number of trips is faithful (e.g., a reliable cloud service has provided the employee's location history and a specific processing code was used to aggregate the data).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.21843969821929932}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.698204040527344e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8519869446754456}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8722997307777405}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.655952453613281e-06}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 13820, "id": "c3d52ddab72e8ce544ed6127a8746c1c13649d7c", "metadata": {"id": "c3d52ddab72e8ce544ed6127a8746c1c13649d7c"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/downloads/xml/hal-03941868.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-03941868.grobid.tei.xml"}